[4] USA - Massachusetts
Date: Mon 1 Apr 2019
Source: Mass Live [abridged, edited]
https://www.masslive.com/news/2019/04/measles-case-diagnosed-in-boston-people-warned-of-possible-exposure.html


The Massachusetts Department of Public Health is issuing a measles warning after a person in the greater Boston area was diagnosed with the disease on Sunday [31 Mar 2019]. The victim went to several public locations while infectious and could have spread the virus to other people.

"The measles virus is currently causing large national and international outbreaks of measles, and a lack of vaccination, combined with domestic and international travel, has resulted in the spread of illness," said Dr. Catherine Brown, Massachusetts state epidemiologist. "Getting vaccinated is the best way to protect yourself from this disease."

