[9] China (Hong Kong) ex Philippines
Date: Mon 1 Apr 2019
Source: GMA News Online [abridged, edited]
https://www.gmanetwork.com/news/pinoyabroad/news/689872/four-filipinos-in-hong-kong-infected-with-measles-amid-outbreak/story/


The Philippine Consul in Hong Kong confirmed that of the 30 people who have been infected with measles in Hong Kong, 6 of them came from the Philippines, and of these 6, 4 are Filipinos working as household helpers.

The 5th person who got infected with measles is a Filipino but his profession was not mentioned. The 6th individual infected, on the other hand, is a foreigner who visited the Philippines.

The measles outbreak has prompted Hong Kong's Department of Food and Health to advise Filipinos who went on vacation in the Philippines to have themselves vaccinated against measles 1st before going back to work in Hong Kong.

The advisory from Hong Kong's Department of Food and Health has also been sent to overseas Filipino worker (OFW) organizations.

A dialogue among Hong Kong's Health department officials and OFW groups has been set to identify clear guidelines on how to implement the policy in light of the outbreak.

Canete said the dialogue is expected to determine whether those who have been vaccinated before would still have to get vaccinated with an anti-measles shot, and who should pay for the anti-measles vaccine of household service workers.

[Byline: Llanesca T. Panti]

