[15] USA - Anti-vaxxer named and shamed by concerned mums in neighbourhood
Date: Sun 31 Mar 2019
Source: 9Honey [abridged, edited]
https://honey.nine.com.au/2019/04/01/13/03/anti-vax-called-out-by-wisconsin-mums?app=applenews


A group of mums in the US have named and shamed their anti-vax neighbour, amid a measles outbreak affecting dozens of states across the country.

The Wisconsin parents penned a letter warning other residents that a local woman "does not believe in vaccinating herself or her family," putting many people in the community at risk.

"This puts anyone at risk if they are medically fragile, immunocompromised, or out of date in their vaccinations," the letter reads. "Please use caution when sharing work or personal space with this individual, eating foods prepared by this individual, or attending gatherings at this individual's house if you or the people who are important to you fall into medically at-risk categories."

Individuals who aren't vaccinated can easily spread diseases like measles to people who are immune-compromised or can't be vaccinated, such as the elderly, patients undergoing chemotherapy, and babies.

The letter addresses this risk, as well as pointing out how the growing anti-vax movement has helped the resurgence of diseases including measles.

People who are unvaccinated have caused outbreaks in Arkansas, Oregon Washington, California, New York, North Carolina, Michigan, Virginia, Texas, Kansas, Illinois, Kentucky, Florida, Minnesota, Colorado, and Pennsylvania, with more outbreaks expected," the letter reads.

"Nearly all outbreaks of disease were started by unvaccinated individuals, who pass along vaccine-preventable diseases to those without adequate protection."

[Byline: Maddison Leach]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[This is rather severe treatment that likely will make the individual targets of the campaign even more recalcitrant and determined to band together with like-minded allies. Perhaps testimony in community meetings, from families who have had children infected with measles, might be more persuasive. - Mod LK]
